He told the delegates every ANC Members needs to be part of the party's structure to push for radical economic transformation. JOHANNESBURG – The African National Congress (ANC) president Jacob Zuma has warned the party to guard against the revolution being taken away from the party. Addressing the uMkhonto weSizwe Military Veterans Association elective conference in Boksburg earlier on Friday Zuma said the ANC must ensure the economy is in the hands of the majority. He told the delegates every ANC Members needs to be part of the party's structure to push for radical economic transformation.   “You have heard about revolutions being taken away from revolutionaries, there are many books. I don’t think we want South Africa to be one of the countries counted in that list. We must defend our revolution; we must make our freedom complete.”